Motiva Enterprises LLC
Norco, Louisiana Refinery
Risk Management Plan (RMP) A? Executive Summary

Motiva Enterprises LLC (or Motiva) operates an oil refinery in Norco, Louisiana.  The following is a list of RMP toxic and flammable substances stored at Motiva:

Flammables: 
- Butene;
- Propane;
- Propylene;
- Butane;
- Isobutane;
- Methane;
- Hydrogen;
- 1,3 Butadiene;
- Ethyl Mercaptan;
- 1-Pentene;

Toxics:
- Hydrochloric Acid;
- Hydrogen Sulfide.

This document provides an overview of various RMP activities at Motiva, including the following:

- A list of RMP regulated substances;
- A summary of potential RMP release scenarios and potential off-site consequences;
- A five-year history of RMP accidental releases of chemicals regulated by EPAA?s RMP rule;
- An overview of emergency response; and 
- An overview of the RMP Accident Prevention Program. 

HSSE MANAGEMENT SYSTEM AND THE RMP PREVENTION PROGRAM 

Motiva maintains a Health, Safety, Security, and Environmental (HSSE) management system and associated policies, procedures, standing instructions, programs and work practices that are related to the RMP Prevention ProgramA?s elements.  

These policies, procedures, standing instructions, programs and work practices are measures that are designed to help the site identify planned changes, which vary at any given time, that are designed to further enhance the siteA?s existing safety programs and procedures.  The following is a summary of some of these measures: 

Employee Participation

The site has an employee participation plan that outlines the various ways that employees can participate, including, for example, the site health and safety committee, Process Hazards Analysis (PHA), incident investigation, and management of change activities.

